<br>
Suliss and Chev are mastered in all languages.  I would like to offer my teaching abilities to any who wish to learn.  I know it is hard for us to set a schedule for this, as so many have varied play times, but I am available most Sunday afternoons and am willing to set aside 2-3 hours to get a group together to learn, if enough show interest.  I think it would be a fun way to get some of the older and younger ones of the family together for a group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   No level limits to learning languages! *smiles*<br>
<br>
So, with that in mind.. I will commit to be in PoK this Sunday from say.. 2:00 pm Central until 4:00 pm Central, and if there is enough interest.. perhaps even extend it to 5 (obviously barring any unforseen RL events that might pre-empt this).  If the times are not convenient for most, I am flexible, but will go with a time that would be beneficial for the most number of people who might be interested.  I also enjoy hunting in the evenings so would like to keep it afternoons if possible.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts or ideas on this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Ueail</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#330000>(8/13/03 6:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Language Fair</span><hr size=1> I think it's a great idea! Could you possibly post that in EST times? :P I have no clue what it would be sooooooo...............Hehe. I will definitely try to be there! *smiles and hugs Chev* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/bchivalrousvalor.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kandiian@chivalrousvalor>kandiian </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#330000>(8/13/03 9:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EST</span><hr size=1> Central is one hour behind eastern, so it is 3 PM to 5 PM EST. I will try to be there however sundays are typically not good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/bchivalrousvalor.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvchev>FV Chev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(8/14/03 12:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/fchivalrousvalorfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Language Fair</span><hr size=1> Thank you Kandiian for posting the Eastern times... I am rather time zone challenged, but I think it would be something like this..<br>
